## Problem Statement
Write a program to sort an array of length 
 using the Quick Sort algorithm. The program should read the array elements and print the array before and after sorting.
---

## Algorithm
1. Start.
2. Read the array elements.
3. Choose the last element as the pivot.
4. Partition the array so that:
5.Elements smaller than or equal to the pivot are on the left.
6. Elements greater than the pivot are on the right.
7. Place the pivot in its correct position.
8. Recursively apply Quick Sort to the left and right subarrays.
9. Repeat until each subarray has one or no elements.
10. Print the sorted array.
11. Stop.
